model	O
are	O
the	O
number	O
of	O
mixture	O
components	O
and	O
the	O
means	O
,	O
variances	O
and	O
priors	O
distributions	O
of	O
these	O
components	O
.	O
In	O
general	O
,	O
the	O
number	O
of	O
mixture	O
components	O
is	O
chosen	O
using	O
some	O
simple	O
ad-hoc	O
rule	O
subject	O
to	O
very	O
loose	O
constraints	O
;	O
for	O
instance	O
the	O
number	O
of	O
components	O
has	O
to	O
be	O
sufficient	O
to	O
model	O
the	O
data	O
reasonably	O
well	O
but	O
not	O
so	O
many	O
as	O
to	O
overmodel	O
the	O
data	O
.	O
A	O
typical	O
example	O
of	O
the	O
choice	O
of	O
the	O
number	O
is	O
to	O
make	O
it	O
proportional	O
to	O
the	O
number	O
of	O
data	O
samples	O
.	O
However	O
,	O
such	O
methods	O
may	O
result	O
in	O
models	O
that	O
are	O
sub-optimal	O
as	O
far	O
as	O
classification	O
accuracy	O
is	O
concerned	O
.	O
For	O
instance	O
,	O
if	O
the	O
number	O
of	O
gaussians	O
